<ent id="sBangkokSilomParsiCemetery"><pi /><names><name language="English">Silom Parsi Cemetery</name><name language="English">Bang Rak Parsi Cemetery</name></names><types><type language="English">cemetery</type><type language="English">Parsi cemetery</type></types><description><div author="Oliver Streiter" language="English">The Silom Parsi Cemetery is a Parsi cemetery in direct vicinity to the Hakka, Hokkien and Cantonese Cemeteries. To enter the cemetery one has to enter the alley to the Cantonese school and push a rolling gate open, which is unlocked during day time. A gardien is living insight the area of the Christian and Parsi Cemetery and he will lock and unlock the cemetery. Within the compound, the cemetery is separated by a fence in two parts, the Christian Cemetery and the Parsi Cemetery. Within the Parsi cemeteries there are a few older Parsi tombs, while newer tombs with Christian or Muslim symbolisms are included. In the center of the areal of the Parsi cemetery is a monument commenmorating the establishment of the cemetery. A simple wooden house on the compound of the Parsi cemetery is where the gardien of the cemeteris lives during day time.</div></description><stats><stat type="tomb" cross="0" direct="4" indirect="0">4</stat></stats><communities><community /></communities><admins><adminsys><admtop>sBangRak</admtop></adminsys></admins><geography geotop="sBangRak" siteid="sBangRak"><street language="English" script="Latin">525 Soi Sueksa Witthaya</street><orientations><orientation system="geographic north">45</orientation></orientations><longitude src="percol-down">100.5258015</longitude><latitude src="percol-down">13.7242585</latitude></geography><culturaldomain /><events><event type="fieldwork" day="2018-02-04" lunar="2017-12-19" /></events></ent>
